label.value: neuromuscular junction of myotube

definition.value: A neuromuscular junction in which the target muscle cell is a myotube.

label.value: neuromuscular junction of somatic muscle myotube

definition.value: A neuromuscular junction in which the target muscle cell is a somatic muscle myotube, such as an arthropod somatic muscle cell.

label.value: excitatory neuromuscular junction of somatic myotube

definition.value: A neuromuscular junction that functions in the excitation of somatic muscle myotubes, such as an arthropod somatic muscle cells.

label.value: inhibitory neuromuscular junction of somatic myotube

definition.value: A neuromuscular junction that functions in the inhibition of somatic muscle myotube contraction. Examples of somatic muscle myotubes include the somatic muscle cells of arthropods.

label.value: neuromuscular junction of somatic muscle

definition.value: A neuromuscular junction in which the target muscle cell is a somatic muscle cell, such as those found in nematodes and arthropods.

label.value: direct ligand regulated sequence-specific DNA binding transcription factor activity

definition.value: A DNA binding transcription factor activity that is directly regulated by binding of a ligand to the protein with this activity.  Examples include the lac and trp repressors in E.coli and many steroid hormone receptors.

label.value: ATPase dependent transmembrane transport complex

definition.value: A transmembrane protein complex that functions in ATPase dependent active transport across a membrane.

label.value: deuterosome

definition.value: A spherical, electron dense, cytoplasmic structure that is involved in de novo assembly of centrioles.

label.value: lobed nucleus

definition.value: Nucleus with two or more lobes connected by a thin filament that contains no internal chromatin.  Examples include the nuclei of mature basophils, eosinophils and neutrophils in mice and humans.

label.value: lumenal side of transport vesicle membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the transport vesicle membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of transport vesicle membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the transport vesicle membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: lumenal side of trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: 2',5-3',5'-cyclic GMP-AMP binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with c[G(2',5')pA(2',5')p], a cyclic purine dinucleotide that consists of AMP and GMP units cyclized via 2',5' and 3',5' linkages.

label.value: lumenal side of Golgi membrane

definition.value: The side of the Golgi membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of Golgi membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the Golgi membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: somatic ring canal

definition.value: A stable intercellular bridge between somatic cells.  Examples include the intercellular bridges between ovarian follicle cells in insects and between imaginal disc cells in insects.

label.value: lumenal side of early endosome membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the early endosome membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: lumenal side of late endosome membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the late endosome membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: side of membrane

definition.value: A cellular component consisting of one leaflet of a membrane bilayer and any proteins embedded or anchored in it or attached to its surface.

label.value: lumenal side of endoplasmic reticulum membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plasma membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of endoplasmic reticulum membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plasma membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: lumenal side of rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: lumenal side of smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of early endosome membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the early endosome membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of late endosome membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the late endosome membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: methyl accepting chemotaxis protein complex

definition.value: A transmembrane protein complex that consists of multiple methyl-accepting chemoreceptor protein subunits, a histidine kinase and a connector protein and which functions in the regulation of flagellar rotary motor activity in response to an external chemical stimulus.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of membrane

definition.value: The side of a membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: intrinsic component of synaptic vesicle membrane

definition.value: The component of the synaptic vesicle membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that have some covalently attached part (e.g. peptide sequence or GPI anchor), which spans or is embedded in one or both leaflets of the membrane.

label.value: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle lumen

definition.value: The volume enclosed within the membrane of a trans-Golgi network transport vesicle.

label.value: lumenal side of endosome membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the endosome membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: transport vesicle lumen

definition.value: The volume enclosed within the membrane of a transport vesicle.

label.value: periplasmic side of plasma membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of a plasma membrane that faces the cytoplasm, and all proteins embedded in it or attached to its surface.

label.value: external side of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the mycolate outer membrane that faces the environment and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: internal side of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The side of the mycolate outer membrane that faces the cell wall peptidoglycan. It is rich in long-chain mycolic acids (hydroxylated branched-chain fatty acids) that are covalently linked to the cell wall peptidoglycan via an arabinogalactan network.

label.value: stromal side of plastid inner membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plastid inner membrane that faces the stroma, and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: lumenal side of plastid thylakoid membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plastid thylakoid membrane that faces the lumen, and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: stromal side of plastid thylakoid membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plastid thylakoid membrane that faces the stroma, and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: intrinsic component of mitochondrial membrane

definition.value: The component of the mitochondrial membrane consisting of the gene products that have some covalently attached part (e.g. peptide sequence or GPI anchor) which spans or is embedded in one or both leaflets of the membrane.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of lysosomal membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the lysosomal membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

label.value: lumenal side of lysosomal membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the lysosomal membrane that faces the lumen.

label.value: lumenal side of membrane

definition.value: Any side (leaflet) of a membrane that faces the lumen of an organelle.

label.value: inactive sex chromosome

definition.value: A sex chromosome that has been inactivated.

label.value: condensed chromatin of inactivated sex chromosome

definition.value: A condensed form of chromatin that is associated with an inactivated sex chromosome and which is responsible for its inactivation.

label.value: active sex chromosome

definition.value: A sex chromosome that has not been inactivated.

label.value: chromatin of active sex chromosome

definition.value: Chromatin that is part of an active sex chromosome.

label.value: host cell synaptic vesicle

definition.value: A secretory organelle of a host cell, some 50 nm in diameter, of presynaptic nerve terminals -  accumulates in high concentrations of neurotransmitters and secretes these into the synaptic cleft by fusion with the 'active zone' of the presynaptic plasma membrane.

label.value: host cell synaptic vesicle membrane

definition.value: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host synaptic vesicle.
